\/\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Divide mixture and shape into eight equal-sized patties. Place onto a baking sheet and chill in freezer 10 minutes."},{"content":"Heat approximately 2 tsp oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook four patties at a time, 2-3 minutes each side, or until heated through and browned. Transfer to a plate and keep warm. Cook remaining patties the same way using 2 tsp oil for frying. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For an egg-free version, replace the egg with 1 tbsp flax seed mixed with 3 tbsp warm water. Whisk together and refrigerate 15 minutes before using.","To freeze uncooked patties: place patties between sheets of wax paper on a baking sheet and freeze. Wrap individually and store in a freezer bag or plastic container. Fry or grill as needed without thawing first.","Patties can be baked for 20 minutes at 400°F until lightly golden."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","8 portions"]}